article.description: — Walter Clayton Jr. had 21 points in Iona's 90-60 win over Canisius on Sunday.
article.headline: Clayton's 21 lead Iona over Canisius 90-60
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. -- — Walter Clayton Jr. had 21 points in Iona's 90-60 win over Canisius on Sunday. Clayton added four steals for the Gaels (4-2). Berrick JeanLouis scored 16 points while finishing 6 of 8 from the floor, and added seven rebounds. Nelly Junior Joseph was 4 of 8 shooting and 4 of 8 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points. Tahj Staveskie led the way for the Golden Griffins (2-6) with 13 points. Canisius also got 11 points from Jamir Moultrie. Jacco Fritz also had 10 points and 13 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
